<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pianist Talks About NYC Concert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- It's all about form for concert pianist Maurizio  
Pollini. 
</P>
<P>
	The famed 57-year-old Italian pianist, often praised for his  
elegant playing, was at Weill Recital Hall Tuesday night to talk 
about ``Perspectives: Maurizio Pollini,'' his concert series at 
Carnegie Hall. 
</P>
<P>
	The pieces, many of which will be performed by Pollini, are  
dedicated to composers of the last half of the 20th century. 
</P>
<P>
	Unlike many groundbreaking masterpieces that used musical forms  
of the past, composers from the 14th century onwards based their 
music on new forms, Pollini said. 
</P>
<P>
	The pianist will play Beethoven, Schoenberg and Stockhausen at  
the first Perspectives concert this Sunday. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
