<HEADLINE> Hornets' Rookie Grant Breaks Hand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- Tyrone Grant, a rookie free agent  
competing for a job with the Charlotte Hornets, broke his left hand 
Friday and will miss the rest of training camp. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-7 Grant, who played at St. John's, was injured when  
he collided with a teammate during a drill. 
</P>
<P>
	The Hornets said Grant was expected to be out at least four  
weeks. 
  	   	
