<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AP Names Editorial Services Head </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Tim Gallivan, a specialist in news technology  
for The Associated Press, has been named to the new position of 
coordinator of editorial services. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced today by Vice President and  
Executive Editor William Ahearn. 
</P>
<P>
	Gallivan, who has been AP's director of news technology, will  
help news managers develop new services for AP members, subscribers 
and commercial clients. He also will coordinate efforts to enhance 
traditional services for member Web sites and other distribution 
channels. 
</P>
<P>
	Gallivan joined the AP in 1979 as an editorial clerk at AP  
headquarters. Three years later he joined a technology group 
responsible for the cooperative's news, election and e-mail 
systems. 
</P>
<P>
	Gallivan has managed that group -- now called News Technology --  
since 1987, first as systems editor, then as director. In 1996 he 
won the Gramling Achievement Award, a $10,000 employee prize, for 
his contribution to the redesign and support of AP's news computer 
systems. 
</P>
<P>
	Gallivan, 49, is a native of Salt Lake City.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
