<HEADLINE> Celtics Welcome Back Russell </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WALTHAM, Mass. (AP) -- Hall of Famer Bill Russell, who won 11 NBA  
championships in 13 years with Boston, will return to the Celtics 
next week to work with the team's big men. 
</P>
<P>
	``I believe in Coach (Rick) Pitino and our Celtic team. They  
have heart, they're smart, they're talented and they have the 
ability to be winners,'' Russell said in a statement released by 
the team. ``If I can be of any help, I'll try.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Russell had remained out of the public eye for much of the time  
since his playing days ended in 1969. But he returned to Boston in 
May for a tribute in his honor, and decided he missed being a part 
of the team. 
</P>
<P>
	``I love the Boston Celtics,'' he said. ``The pride I feel for  
the uniform, my teammates, my coach and our fans -- Celtic pride -- 
is a way of life.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Russell was expected to observe the team at practice on Sunday  
and work with the players Monday and Tuesday. Practice is closed to 
the public. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
