<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are moving substantially or trading  
heavily Friday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	
</P>
<P>
 *Xerox Corp., down 10 1/4 at 32 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	The Stamford, Conn.-based copier maker expects its third-quarter  
earnings to fall below Wall Street analysts' estimates and its 
revenues to be flat with a year ago. Xerox said the shortfall was 
due to weaker-than-expected sales in the United States and Europe 
and increased competition. 

</P>
<P>
 *Consolidated Papers Inc., up 1 15/16 at 29 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The Wisconsin Rapids, Wis.-based company, which makes printing  
paper, reported third-quarter earnings that surpassed Wall Street 
analysts' expectations. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Hi/fn Inc., down 36 1/4 at 37 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	The Los Gatos, Calif.-based semiconductor maker said two major  
customers -- Lucent Technologies Inc. and Quantum Corp. -- cut back 
their purchases, which will hurt Hi/fn's revenues. 

</P>
<P>
 *24/7 Media, up 6 7/8 at 47 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Online advertiser 24/7 Media is in talks to be bought by  
competitor DoubleClick, according to the Web site 
siliconalleyreporter.com. 

</P>
<P>
 *Triangle Pharmaceuticals Inc., down 5 3/8 at 15 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The Durham, N.C.-based company modified its clinical study of  
the AIDS drug Coactinon after problems when it was combined with 
another drug. That could delay the company's application with the 
Food and Drug Administration to market the drug. 

</P>
<P>
 *Landmark Systems Corp., down 2 1/8 at 6 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The Reston, Va.-based business software maker expects  
third-quarter earnings to fall below Wall Street analysts' 
estimates. The company said the shortfall was due to its failure to 
make several large sales. 

</P>
<P>
 *CareMatrix Corp., down 2 13/16 at 3 15/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The Needham, Mass.-based company, which runs senior housing and  
assisted living facilities, expects its third-quarter earnings to 
fall below Wall Street analysts' estimates. The company said the 
shortfall was due to decrease in development activity. 




  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
