<HEADLINE> Trainer: Horses Make Me Look Good </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- James Bond is a trainer, not a jockey, who  
sounds like he's just along for the ride with Behrens. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's a horse that makes you look good,'' Bond said of  
5-year-old Behrens, who can take another step toward Horse of the 
Year honors by winning the 1 1/4-mile Jockey Club Gold Cup on Sunday 
at Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's always been a good horse and now he's matured into a  
great horse,'' Bond said. 
</P>
<P>
	Behrens won consecutive stakes before losing by a nose to the  
now-retired Victory Gallop in the Whitney Handicap in his last 
start Aug. 1 at Saratoga. 
</P>
<P>
	Behrens will face eight rivals in the $1 million Gold Cup, but  
the one getting the most attention is 3-year-old Lemon Drop Kid, 
winner of the Belmont Stakes and the Travers, who will be making 
his debut against older horses. 
</P>
<P>
	Another attraction on the card will be sensational 3-year-old  
filly Silverbulletday, a winner in eight of nine starts this year. 
Silverbulletday will be racing for the first time against older 
fillies and mares in the 1 1/8-mile Beldame. 
</P>
<P>
	She will face four rivals, two of them being 4-year-olds  
Beautiful Pleasure, winner of the Personal Ensign at Saratoga, and 
Catinca, winner of the Ruffian at Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Two others Lemon Drop Kid will have to overcome are River Keen,  
winner of the Woodward at Belmont, and Almutawakel, winner of the 
Dubai World Cup and second in the Woodward. Two other 3-year-olds 
in the Gold Cup are Vision and Verse, second in both the Belmont 
Stakes and Travers, and Stephen Got Even, third in the Woodward. 
</P>
<P>
	The 3-year-olds will carry 123 pounds, the others 126.  
</P>
<P>
	In the $500,000 Beldame, the 3-year-olds will carry 119 pounds,  
the rest 123. 
</P>
<P>
	In a third Grade I stakes, Finder's Fee, the Matron winner, will  
oppose four other 2-year-old fillies in the $400,000 Frizette over 
1 1-16 miles. 
</P>
<P>
	Today's features at Belmont were the 1 1-16-mile Champagne for  
2-year-olds and the 1 1/2-mile Turf Classic. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
