<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Yanks LCS Tickets Go on Sale Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Tickets for the New York Yankees second-round  
playoff series go on sale Sunday beginning at 1 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
	The Yankees, who lead the Texas Rangers 2-0 in their best-of-5  
series, will advance to the AL championship series by beating Texas 
once in the next three games. 
</P>
<P>
	If the Yankees advance, they will play host to the first two  
games, Oct. 13-14 at 8:15 p.m., and games six and seven, if 
necessary, Oct. 20-21. 
</P>
<P>
	Tickets for the first two games can be bought only at Yankee  
Stadium. Randomly numbered wristbands will be distributed beginning 
at 8 a.m.. Shortly after 11 a.m., a randomly selected starting 
number will be chosen and the person holding that numbered 
wristband will be first in line to purchase tickets. 
</P>
<P>
	Those holding bands with numbers following the starting point  
will be served in numerical order. Those holding numbers below the 
starting point will go to the rear of the line. 
</P>
<P>
	For tickets to the sixth and seventh games, fans must call  
TicketMaster at (212) 307-1212, beginning at 1 p.m. A service 
charge will be added to all phone orders. 
</P>
<P>
	A maximum of four tickets can be purchased. Tickets are priced  
at $70 for box seats, $50 for reserve and $30 for bleachers. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
