<HEADLINE> US Advances in Wrestling Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANKARA, Turkey (AP) -- Joe Williams advanced to the semifinals  
and fellow American Eric Guerrero won his match Friday in the World 
Freestyle Wrestling Championships. 
</P>
<P>
	Williams, of Iowa City, Iowa, defeated Korea's Moon Eui-Jae in  
the 167 1/2-pound class in 5 minutes, 7 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
	Guerrero, ranked No. 2 in the United States at 127 3/4 pounds, beat  
Algeria's Mohamed Amine by technical fall 10-0. 
</P>
<P>
	The 22-year old Guerrero then defeated French wrestler Leprince  
David with 7-3 decision. Guerrero had replaced two-time World 
Champion Terry Brands, who is ill. He will face Todorov Sevdalin of 
Bulgaria in fourth round on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Turkey's Adem Bereket also advanced to the semifinals with an  
upset over Elsad Allahverdiyev, 4-3. 
</P>
<P>
	1997 World Champion Les Gutches of the United States pinned  
Chech Rudolf Voboril in 3 minutes, 31 seconds to advance at the 187 
-pound division. Gutches, of Colorado Springs, Colo., will face 
Lithunia's Egidisus Vielavicius Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	U.S. wrestler Stephen Neal, Bakersfield, Calif., also advanced  
to the fourth round at 286 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
	The championship serves as the first freestyle wrestling  
qualifier for the 2000 Olympics in Sydney, Australia. The top eight 
at the 1999 World Championships qualify to participate in the 
Olympics in their weight division. 
</P>
<P>
	A total of 64 Olympic berths will be determined at the end of  
the games. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
