<HEADLINE> Man Charged in Deaths of 3 Kids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LINDSBORG, Kan. (AP) -- A man was arrested in the killings of his  
three children during an attack that also left his wife bloodied 
and screaming for help, authorities and witnesses said. 
</P>
<P>
	Chris Jones, 47, was charged with three counts of first-degree  
murder and one of aggravated assault. He was under guard at a 
hospital Thursday where he underwent surgery to repair a gash on 
his throat. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities would not discuss details of the case or how the  
Jones children were killed. Neighbors identified two of the 
children as Christopher, 7, and Joshua, 5. The third was a 
2-year-old girl. 
</P>
<P>
	Neighbors said Jones' wife, Cathy, ran out of the family's home  
drenched in blood Wednesday night crying for help. 
</P>
<P>
	Neighbor Jack White said she screamed, ``He is after me.''  
</P>
<P>
	Cathy Jones, 34, had a gash on her head, a cut on her hand and  
stab wounds to her chest, neighbors said. She was hospitalized in 
Lindsborg in fair condition Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities found the children's bodies inside the home.  
</P>
<P>
	Neighbor Julie Harding said the father was unemployed and on  
most days could be seen walking the children to school. 
</P>
<P>
	``Here we are sitting in our home, our lives going normally, and  
their lives are ripped apart,'' she said. 
</P>
<P>
	Lindsborg, a town of 4,000, is about 100 miles southwest of  
Topeka. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
