<HEADLINE> Genentech Shares Tumble </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SOUTH SAN FRANCISCO, Calif. (AP) -- Genentech Inc. shares tumbled  
Friday after disclosing its controlling shareholder, Roche Holdings 
Inc., plans to sell a 15.6 percent stake in the biotechnology firm. 
</P>
<P>
	Roche, the Swiss pharmaceuitcal maker which controls about 83  
percent of Genentech, plans to sell about 22 million Genentech 
shares on the open market. 
</P>
<P>
	In trading, Genentech shares were down $15.06 1/4 a share, or 8.7  
percent, to $157.75 on the New York Stock Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
	At that price, the 22 million Genentech shares would be worth  
about $3.47 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Genentech, which makes growth hormones and treatments for  
non-Hodgkin's lymphoma and cystic fibrosis, made the disclosure 
about Roche's plans as it reported Thursday a 6 percent rise in 
earnings before charges for the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich, Roche Holding confirmed Friday it will sell up to 22  
million shares of Genentech and issue a $1 billion, zero-coupon 
bond exchangeable into another 5.5 million of Genentech shares. 
</P>
<P>
	It would still have about a 65 percent stake in Genentech after  
the planned sales. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
