<P>
	$730M Award in State Farm Lawsuit  
</P>
<P>
	MARION, Ill. (AP) -- A judge awarded $730 million to State Farm  
policyholders in a class-action lawsuit over its use of 
questionable auto-body repair parts, adding to a $456 million jury 
award already believed to be the largest ever against an insurance 
company. The award includes $130 million in punitive damages on 
policyholders' claims that the nation's largest auto insurer 
deliberately deceived customers about the quality of ``aftermarket 
parts'' it requires body shops to use in repairs. 

</P>
<P>
	Stocks End Higher; Dow Up 112.71  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks rose today as investors brushed off  
concerns about rising inflation and turned their focus toward the 
positive earnings news expected next week. At the close of trading 
on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was up 112.71 at 
10,649.76. For the week, the blue-chip index gained more than 376 
points, its biggest weekly rise since early July. Broader stock 
indicators also rose. The Nasdaq composite index gained 21.76 to 
2,882.46. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
Dow Industrials:        10,649.76  + 112.71
