<HEADLINE> Stephen King Donating $40,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	STONEHAM, Maine (AP) -- Stephen King's charity is donating  
$40,000 to help buy a new ambulance for a rescue service that came 
to the novelist's aid this summer. 
</P>
<P>
	It was just the latest in a string of high-priced thank yous the  
horror writer has sent since he was hit by a van as he walked along 
a rural road near his home in Lovell. 
</P>
<P>
	King earlier announced he would give $100,000 each to Central  
Maine Medical Center and Northern Cumberland Memorial Hospital in 
Bridgton -- the two hospitals where he was treated. 
</P>
<P>
	The Stoneham Rescue Service, the first to reach King, has been  
struggling to raise money for a new ambulance for nearly a year. 
  	   	
</P>
