<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Canada 2, El Salvador 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Carl Fletcher scored in the 60th minute  
Friday night to give Canada a 2-1 victory over El Salvador in the 
CONCACAF Gold Cup qualifying tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	In the first game of the doubleheader, Johny Descolines' second  
goal of the tournament gave Haiti a 1-0 victory over Cuba. 
</P>
<P>
	As a result, Canada and Haiti lead the four-team group with four  
points apiece, while Cuba and El Salvador each have one. The top 
two teams from the round-robin tournament qualify for February's 
CONCACAF Gold Cup, the North American championship. 
</P>
<P>
	The Gold Cup ends Sunday with Canada playing Haiti and El  
Salvador facing Cuba. 
</P>
<P>
	Fletcher broke a 1-1 tie when he took a pass from Marc Bircham  
15 yards from the goal line, dribbled toward the edge of the 
18-yard penalty area and fired a shot inside the right post. 
</P>
<P>
	Carlo Corazzin gave Canada a 1-0 lead in the 10th minute, but  
Raul Diaz Arce tied the score with a penalty kick in the 47th 
minute. 
</P>
<P>
	El Salvador played with 10 men over the final 52 minutes after  
playmaker Mauricio Cienfuegos was ejected for thrusting his cleats 
toward Fletcher's midsection. 
</P>
<P>
	Though Cienfuegos did not make contact, referee Armando  
Archundia issued a red card. Cienfuegos, who plays for Major League 
Soccer's Los Angeles Galaxy, shares the MLS lead in assists with 
17. 
</P>
<P>
	Descolines scored in the 75th minute when he outmaneuvered Cuban  
sweeper Tobio Mora after taking a pass and kicked a 15-yard shot 
into the upper right corner of the net. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
